info.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued February 22 at 2:20PM CST until February 23 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...WIND CHILL ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 11 PM THIS EVENING TO NOON CST THURSDAY... * WHAT...Very cold wind chills expected. Wind chills as low as 35 below zero. * WHERE...Koochiching, North St. Louis, Northern Cook and Lake, North Itasca and Southern Cook Counties. This includes the Tribal Lands of the Grand Portage Reservation and the Bois Forte Band, Deer Creek and, Nett Lake areas. * WHEN...From 11 PM this evening to noon CST Thursday. * IMPACTS...The dangerously cold wind chills could cause frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes.
info.instruction: Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a hat, and gloves.
